The global Food Grade Potassium Chloride market was valued at US$ million in 2022 and is projected to reach US$ million by 2029, at a CAGR of % during the forecast period.

Food grade potassium chloride is used in foods for human consumption. It is an important component of mineral-rich drinks and is employed in the processing of gelatin, fish, and canned vegetables. It also serves as a substitute for table salt in low sodium products.

